{"slug": "croak_and_dagger", "name": "Croak and Dagger", "commander": "Glarb, Calamity's Augur", "colors": "Sultai", "pips": ["U", "B", "G"], "archetype": "Topdeck combo-control", "status": "Elite", "bracket": 3, "score": 18, "axes": [{"label": "Core loop", "score": 5}, {"label": "Kill reliability", "score": 5}, {"label": "Durability", "score": 4}, {"label": "Interaction", "score": 4}], "axesTotal": "18/20", "gc": ["Bolas's Citadel", "Fierce Guardianship", "Seedborn Muse"], "kicker": "In the Sultai corner", "corner": "Bracket 3 \u00b7 Sultai", "tagline": "Sensei's Top + any top-caster (Bolas's Citadel / One with the Multiverse / Fortune Teller's Talent / The Reality Chip) + Aetherflux Reservoir -> loop the library -> Pay 50: deal 50 (counter-immune); Torment of Hailfire grind backup", "colorLine": "Sultai \u00b7 UBG", "idea": "The deck assembles a redundant \"Topdeck Matters\" loop and converts it into a counter-immune burst.", "vitals": [{"label": "Clock", "value": "T9", "accent": true, "sub": "decap T9"}, {"label": "Decap", "value": "T9", "sub": "one opponent"}, {"label": "Game Changers", "value": "3/3", "sub": "bracket-3 cap"}], "briefKillsCaption": "the lines that win", "briefKills": [{"idx": "01", "tag": "combo", "primary": true, "clock": "table T9", "line": "Sensei's Top + a top-caster (Bolas's Citadel / One with the Multiverse / Fortune Teller's L2 / Reality Chip) + Aetherflux Reservoir \u2192 loop Top casts \u2192 bank 50+ life \u2192 Pay 50: deal 50 to each opponent (a counter-immune ability)"}, {"idx": "02", "tag": "combo", "primary": false, "clock": "table T9", "line": "same loop, Ancient Cellarspawn as the payoff (drain on each under-costed cast) \u2192 every free / discounted Top recast drains an opponent \u2192 table (redundant 2nd payoff)"}], "openings": ["Weakest axis \u2014 Durability (4/5): the judges' soft spot.", "Redundant 3-category combo (4 enablers x 2 payoffs); ramp -> Torment is the MANA-gated backup.", "Decap never-closes in 10% of goldfish games \u2014 a grind risk.", "Tables (all three) never-close 10% of the time."], "clock": {"decap": "T9", "table": "T9", "grid": [4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 12, 14], "decapCurve": [0, 2, 9, 24, 41, 55, 66, 82, 90], "tableCurve": [0, 2, 9, 24, 41, 55, 66, 82, 90], "never": [10, 10], "src": "lab glarb_inevitable_lab FULL @20k on croak-and-dagger-20260701.txt (honest dig=selection; 2026-07-01 promotion)", "sub": "measured kill-clock", "headline": [{"label": "Decap \u00b7 one opp", "value": "T9", "sub": "median kill", "kind": "decap"}, {"label": "Table \u00b7 all three", "value": "T9", "sub": "median kill", "kind": "table"}], "bands": [{"label": "decap", "from": 9, "to": 9, "kind": "decap"}, {"label": "table", "from": 9, "to": 9, "kind": "table"}], "ticks": [4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 14], "axisFrom": 4, "axisTo": 14, "note": "", "noteLabel": "", "caption": "Decap (one opponent) lands around T9; the full table around T9."}, "gamePlan": "The deck assembles a redundant \"Topdeck Matters\" loop and converts it into a counter-immune burst. **Sensei's Divining Top** ({T}: draw a card, then put Top back on top of the library) is the loop core; any **no-mana-value-restriction top-caster** \u2014 Bolas's Citadel (pay life = mana value), One with the Multiverse (one free cast/turn), Fortune Teller's Talent at level 2, or The Reality Chip \u2014 lets you recast Top off the top each iteration, chaining through the library. With a **payoff** online \u2014 Aetherflux Reservoir (gain 1 life per spell cast this turn, then \"Pay 50 life: deal 50 to any target,\" an *ability* that can't be countered) or Ancient Cellarspawn (drain an opponent on every under-costed cast) \u2014 the loop banks arbitrary life and flings 50 at each opponent, or drains the table one cast at a time. Inevitability comes from **redundancy, not one combo**: four interchangeable enablers \u00d7 two payoffs, stacked onto the top by non-GC topdeck tutors (Insidious Dreams, Emergent Ultimatum, Scheming Symmetry) and fed by Glarb's surveil, Sylvan Library, and Oracle of Mul Daya. Underneath the combo sits the old grind shell \u2014 38 lands, Cabal Coffers + Urborg, and **Torment of Hailfire** as a board-independent X-drain backup for the ~10% of games the combo bricks \u2014 plus a full counter suite and **Tidal Barracuda** (a one-sided Grand Abolisher on your own turn) to protect the kill.", "winLine": "Sensei's Top + any top-caster (Bolas's Citadel / One with the Multiverse / Fortune Teller's Talent / The Reality Chip) + Aetherflux Reservoir -> loop the library -> Pay 50: deal 50 (counter-immune); Torment of Hailfire grind backup", "finishers": [{"name": "Aetherflux loop", "tag": "primary, combo", "note": "Sensei's Divining Top + any top-caster (Bolas's Citadel / One with the Multiverse / Fortune Teller's Talent L2 / The Reality Chip) + **Aetherflux Reservoir** all in play."}, {"name": "Cellarspawn drain", "tag": "combo, redundant payoff", "note": "the same loop with **Ancient Cellarspawn** as the payoff \u2014 every free/discounted Top recast (mana spent < mana value) drains the difference from an opponent, grinding the table out one cast at a time."}, {"name": "Topdeck-tutored assembly", "tag": "enabler", "note": "Insidious Dreams (discard X \u2192 stack X cards on top in any order), Emergent Ultimatum (find 3 monocolored, cast 2 free), or Scheming Symmetry stacks the missing loop category on top for Glarb/Citadel; GSZ / Chord / Finale fetch the creature pieces (Ancient Cellarspawn, The Reality Chip)."}, {"name": "Torment of Hailfire", "tag": "grind backup", "note": "X=12+ off ~14 mana via Cabal Coffers + Urborg \u2014 a board-independent table drain for the ~10% of games the combo never assembles."}, {"name": "Value grind", "tag": "fallback", "note": "Seedborn Muse + Glarb top-casting deploy Archon of Cruelty / Massacre Wurm and grind a focused opponent out when nothing else is up."}], "rulings": [{"name": "The Top loop needs a no-MV-restriction top-caster", "note": "Bolas's Citadel / One with the Multiverse / Fortune Teller's Talent (level 2) / The Reality Chip. Glarb alone cannot recast Sensei's Top (it's MV1, and his top-cast is restricted to MV4+); Glarb digs and casts the big pieces, the enabler runs the Top loop."}, {"name": "Aetherflux Reservoir", "note": "gains \"1 life for each spell you've cast this turn\" (escalating \u2014 the nth cast this turn gains n), and \"Pay 50 life: deal 50 damage to any target\" is an activated ability \u2014 it can't be countered and hits one target per activation, so bank the life, then fling 50 at each opponent in turn."}, {"name": "Bolas's Citadel", "note": "casts from the top cost life equal to mana value (not mana). Watch your life total; get the payoff / lifegain online before digging deep."}, {"name": "Tidal Barracuda", "note": "\"your opponents can't cast spells during your turn\" (a one-sided Grand Abolisher that protects the combo turn), but it also lets any player cast at flash, so opponents gain flash on their turns. Combo on your own turn."}, {"name": "Ancient Cellarspawn", "note": "drains only when mana spent < mana value \u2014 it needs a free or discounted cast (One with the Multiverse's free cast, Savvy Trader / Fortune Teller L3 reductions) to trigger; a normally-paid spell does nothing."}, {"name": "Emergent Ultimatum", "note": "finds three monocolored cards with different names; an opponent shuffles one back and you cast the other two for free \u2014 Glarb, most tutors, and the payoffs are monocolored, so grab an enabler + a payoff."}, {"name": "Seedborn Muse", "note": "untaps Glarb and all your lands on every opponent's turn \u2014 surveil, hold up counters, and free-cast off the top each turn cycle without skipping development."}, {"name": "Valley Floodcaller", "note": "flash-enables your noncreature spells and untaps Glarb (a Frog) on each noncreature cast \u2014 chain surveils and casts in a single turn."}], "composition": [{"name": "Game Changers", "count": 3, "win": false}, {"name": 